The Human Rights Commission and Sadtu have raised concern over delays in the delivery of school essentials. JOHANNESBURG The Limpopo Basic Education Department says it will deliver all outstanding stationary to schools by the end of next week.The Human Rights Commission and teacher's union Sadtu have raised concern over delays in the delivery of school essentials.Sadtu handed MEC Ishmael Kgetjepe a memorandum on Thursday demanding that he address the supply shortages and that teachers be given their due employee benefits. By next week we will have cleared everything so that schools have stationary. Kgetjepe says officials are hard at work to ensure all the problems are resolved